      "lesson title": "Smart Factories and AI Attack Surfaces",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Smart factories rely on interconnected machines, sensors, and software systems that communicate constantly, and this connectivity, whilst powerful, creates new opportunities for attackers to exploit. This lesson introduces the concept of attack surfaces and explains how adding more connected devices and AI-driven systems to a factory environment can expand the number of potential entry points for cyber threats. You will explore how traditional industrial equipment, once isolated from external networks, now faces risks that were previously associated only with office IT systems. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why securing a smart factory requires thinking beyond conventional cybersecurity approaches and considering the unique vulnerabilities that AI and automation introduce.",
